Health Preservation &amp; Nuke versus Heatlh Preservation &amp; Nuke<br>
<br>
I think anyone who has more than 10 days played could figure out which of these is the better setup.  If you have a shield of auras the rod regen from heart becomes null and void.  If your getting hit the regen from heart becomes null and void because of the rune...and if that doesn't quite save you than Transon's Phantasmal Protection will serve you just fine.<br>
<br>
So...with the main hand slot freed from the bounds of regen you can put a new, better item there.  Well.. the nuke scepter &gt; BoBC + pretty damn nice stats.<br>
<br>
Why is the nuke scepter better than nuke boots even though the DPS on boots is better?  One word...casting time.  well..two..  f*ck you..  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->      17 seconds on boots is a very, very long time.  Anyone that has epic or boots can tell you this.    I haven't done any math that proves that over time and a % of resist that the sceptre will come out ahead but in my head it seems to make sense that it would.<br>
<br>
Well..so..now you have rod dmg and dmg absortion taken care of.  Manaless nukes taken care of.  And hey!  You have room for some glorious boots of greatness.  Awsome..happiness for all!<br>
<br>
