<br>
For those that say &quot;but cyd, zlandicars is only 2 mana/tic (stacking with all FT,) and with outside heals/SoA I have so much mana regen, and so doesn't matter&quot; I say, &quot;Well then, no loot matters.&quot; The reason +hps is so good is it speeds up mana regen too. But it doesn't speed it up THAT fast. 100 hps is only about 40 mana per full CH landed, and how often do you get CHs landing faster than once every 2 minutes over a long period of time? It happens, but not THAT often.<br>
<br>
That said, you'll probally want at least one of the three (sceptre, bobc, or SoA) for when all the healers die or soloing. SoA is probally out of grasp for awhile, so that leaves bobc and sceptre. Both will eventually become obsolete. Sceptre conflicts with zlandicar's, but the sceptre has beefy hps (almost +100) which partly makes up for the lost regen. Boots conflict with KT boots (probally still unavailable) and FT 3 boots (available if you have the cash). Stats on FT3 boots and velk are basically the same (velk has some more +MR and +int I think)<br>
<br>
Boots have a higher DPS, and contrary to Myr's suggestion, are sometimes resisted LESS then fire (Ssra, Akheva and CT come to mind.) Sceptre does have a big advantage though: it's fast. Using the boots locks you down for 17 seconds, which can be an eternity. The 8 seconds on the sceptre is much more reasonable for squeezing nukes in. OTOH boots are better for pulling when soloing (since you get a nice big nuke up front.) All in all its a matter of taste; I have both, and have used both before I got my SoA. Roughly speaking, I considered the boots better for soloing and raiding, the sceptre better for groups (and certain raids) -- but groups usually have a cleric or shaman, so you shouldn't be using the sceptre anyway. Drop rods. Usually the same in raids, but sometimes healers get distracted. So I'd consider the boots slightly better; however the sacrificed item for boots (FT 3) is more significant then the item you must sacrifice for sceptre (zlandicars = FT2, and you get 100 hps off the sceptre)<br>
<br>
So, I recomend you grab whichever one comes first.<br>
